# lodor#7 dot-hidden disc folder (hardware-confirmed UX fix): the engine writes discs
# into ".<Game>/" beside the .m3u (hidden from MinUI-family game lists) with
# ".<Game>/…" playlist lines. A launcher can hand the hook a DISC PATH inside that
# folder (getFirstDisc-style launches); m3u_for must DOT-STRIP the folder name to
# resolve the sibling "<Game>.m3u", and from there the standard incomplete-set
# re-trigger runs: --check-rom says incomplete -> --fetch-next-disc lands disc 2
# (via the dot-relative playlist line) -> launch proceeds.
desc fetch hook (lodor#7 dot folder): disc-path launch inside ".<Game>/" resolves the sibling m3u
invoke prehook
config paired
romarg Roms/PlayStation (PS)/.FF7/D1.chd
sdtext Roms/PlayStation (PS)/FF7.m3u	.FF7/D1.chd\n.FF7/D2.chd\n
sdfile+ Roms/PlayStation (PS)/.FF7/D1.chd
sdfile Roms/PlayStation (PS)/.FF7/D2.chd
engine 0|RESULT complete=0 discs_total=2 discs_present=1
engine 0|RESULT fetched=1 complete=1 discs_total=2 discs_present=2
engine 0|RESULT complete=1 discs_total=2 discs_present=2
engine 0|
expect_exit 0
expect_trace ENGINE --check-rom
expect_trace ENGINE --fetch-next-disc
expect_file_has Roms/PlayStation (PS)/.FF7/D2.chd	DISCBYTES
